data.chText: 察觉
data.enText: be/become aware

data.chText: 理解；领会；认识到；意识到

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to understand or become aware of a particular fact or situation

data.chText: 我没有察觉到你那么不开心。
data.enText: I didn't realize (that) you were so unhappy.

data.chText: 我一看到她，就觉得不太对劲。
data.enText: The moment I saw her, I realized something was wrong.

data.chText: 我认为你没有意识到这对她是多么重要。
data.enText: I don't think you realize how important this is to her.

data.chText: 形势比他们最初意识到的更为复杂。
data.enText: The situation was more complicated than they had at first realized.

data.chText: 我们谁也没注意，他们悄悄走了。
data.enText: They managed to leave without any of us realizing.

data.chText: 我希望你能认识到这一罪行的严重性。
data.enText: I hope you realize the seriousness of this crime.

data.chText: 只是到了后来她才意识到自己的错误。
data.enText: Only later did she realize her mistake.

data.chText: 人们意识到大家都已平安归来的时候便发出了一阵欢呼声。
data.enText: There was a cheer when it was realized that everyone was safely back.

data.chText: 实现
data.enText: achieve sth

data.chText: 实现；将…变为现实
data.enText: to achieve sth important that you very much want to do

data.chText: 她从未能实现成为一名职业歌手的志向。
data.enText: She never realized her ambition of becoming a professional singer.

data.chText: 我们努力帮助所有的学生充分发挥他们的潜力。
data.enText: We try to help all students realize their full potential (= be as successful as they are able to be) .

data.chText: 发生
data.enText: happen

data.chText: （所担心的事）发生，产生
data.enText: if sb's fears are realized , the things that they are afraid will happen do happen

data.chText: 他一看门被撬了，就知道最担心的事还是发生了。
data.enText: His worst fears were realized when he saw that the door had been forced open.

data.chText: 出售
data.enText: sell

data.chText: 把（财产等）变卖，变现
data.enText: to sell things that you own, for example property, in order to get the money that you need for sth

data.chText: 以…价格卖出
data.enText: to be sold for a particular amount of money

data.chText: 这些绘画在拍卖会上卖出了200万元。
data.enText: The paintings realized $2 million at auction.

data.chText: 使成为现实
data.enText: make sth real

data.chText: 把（概念等）具体表现出来
data.enText: to produce sth that can be seen or heard, based on written information or instructions

data.chText: 舞台设计得到了完美的体现。
data.enText: The stage designs have been beautifully realized.

means: 把（概念等）具体表现出来

ex.zh: 充分认识到；充分发挥出

example: I just can't see your point
Does she realize how important this decision is?

tr: be fully aware or cognizant of

example: our ideas must be substantiated into actions

tr: expand or complete (a part in a piece of baroque music) by supplying the harmonies indicated in the figured bass
earn on some commercial or business transaction
example: How much do you make a month in your new job?
She earns a lot in her new job
this merger brought in lots of money

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 realise

value.def: If you realize that something is true, you become aware of that fact or understand it.

example.ex: As soon as we realised something was wrong, we moved the children away...
example.tran: 我们刚意识到有什么不对劲就把孩子转移了。

example.ex: People don't realize how serious this recession has actually been...
example.tran: 人们没有意识到这次经济衰退事实上有多严重。

example.ex: Once they realised their mistake the phone was reconnected again...
example.tran: 他们一意识到他们的错误，电话就重新接通了。
“那是我弟弟。”——“哦，我没认出来呀。”

example.ex: There is now a growing realisation that things cannot go on like this for much longer...
example.tran: 现在人们越来越认识到事情不能再像这样发展了。

example.ex: He nearly cried out at the sudden realization of how much Randall looked like him.
example.tran: 当他意识到兰德尔和自己有多么相像时，几乎叫了出来。

value.def: If your hopes, desires, or fears are realized, the things that you hope for, desire, or fear actually happen.

example.ex: Straightaway our worst fears were realised...
example.tran: 我们最恐惧的事情一下发生了。

example.ex: Those are our hopes; we are starting this clinical trial to investigate whether those hopes will be realised.
example.tran: 那些就是我们的希望；我们正在开展这些临床试验以调查那些希望是否可以实现。

value.tran: （希望、心愿或恐惧）实现，成为现实，发生

value.def: When someone realizes a design or an idea, they make or organize something based on that design or idea.

example.ex: Various textile techniques will be explored to realise design possibilities...
example.tran: 将尝试和探索纺织技巧来把这些设计变为现实。

example.ex: The kaleidoscopic quality of the book is brilliantly realised on stage.
example.tran: 该书包罗万象、精彩纷呈的特质在舞台上得到了精彩再现。

value.def: If someone or something realizes their potential, they do everything they are capable of doing, because they have been given the opportunity to do so.

example.ex: The support systems to enable women to realize their potential at work are seriously inadequate...
example.tran: 使妇女在工作中发挥潜力的支持体系严重不足。

example.ex: I think probably that the laser has not realised the potential that was expected of it in that domain.
example.tran: 我想可能激光在那个领域并没有充分发挥其潜力。

value.def: If something realizes a particular amount of money when it is sold, that amount of money is paid for it.

example.ex: A selection of correspondence from P G Wodehouse realised £ 1,232.
example.tran: P.G.沃德豪斯的书信选集卖了1,232英镑。

example.ex: I have taken this course solely to assist the realisation of my assets for the benefit of all my creditors.
example.tran: 我采取这种行动只是为了变现我的资产以偿清欠款。
